    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-10-28T00:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1011"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1011">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/16269: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Chungking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-28T12:00:00+07:00"
                            >October 28, 1940—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October 28—7:25
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>547. My 546, October 26, 1 p.m.,<note n="46" xml:id="d1011fn46">Not
                        printed.</note> bombing of Chungking, October 26. The Ford sedan of the
                    American Assistant Naval Attaché valued at approximately 500 dollars United
                    States currency was completely destroyed during the attack on the lower district
                    of the city. Other American properties apparently escaped without damage.</p>
                <p>Sent to the Department. Repeated to Peiping, Hankow and Shanghai. Shanghai please
                    repeat to Tokyo.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Johnson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
